[If the epidemic were to continue at the current rate of cases per day, by the end of 2017, there could be 700 000 more cases for a total of 1.12 million cases since the end of April 2017 with 3300 more deaths for a total of about 5500 deaths over that time period.

The statistics related to this record-breaking epidemic of _V. cholerae_ in Yemen are shown below:

